Package civitas.celestis.math.real

Class MutableRealVector

java.lang.Object
civitas.celestis.math.real.MutableRealVector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Numeric, RealVector, Serializable
public class MutableRealVector extends Object implements RealVector
A mutable vector class with an adjustable length.

    • multiply

      @Nonnull public MutableRealVector multiply(@Nonnull RealVector v) throws UnsupportedOperationException
      Multiplication is not supported for this vector by default.

      While it is possible to perform multiplication if the length of the vectors is either 2 of 4, this is not implemented due to the performance overhead caused by the mutability of this vector and the non-primitive nature of RealNumber.

      Custom behavior can be implemented by extending this class.

      Specified by:
      multiply in interface RealVector
      Parameters:
      v - The vector to multiply this vector by
      Returns:
      This method cannot return a value
      Throws:
      UnsupportedOperationException - Always throws an exception
